---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Compare', url: '/compare' },
  { name: 'BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper', url: '/compare/breederhq-vs-easykeeper' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Is BreederHQ a good alternative to EasyKeeper for goat breeders?',
    answer: 'It depends on what part of your operation is under-served today. EasyKeeper is goats-only, web-only, and deep on herd operations (kidding, milk production, lactation, DHIR integration, health, tasks, reporting). EasyKeeper Essentials is $19/month or $209/year and Performance is $27/month or $297/year per easykeeper.com/plans-and-pricing, verified July 1, 2026. BreederHQ is a multi-species platform (goats plus 8 more species) with native iOS and Android apps, a transactional public marketplace, per-buyer client portal, per-litter and per-animal financial attribution, rules-based automation for offspring lifecycles, an embed widget that keeps your own website in sync, and Scout AI that reads lab PDFs and vet invoices into records. If dairy-goat DHIR is your center of gravity, EasyKeeper is the more specialized tool. If you run goats plus another species, or you want a marketplace and buyer flow attached to your operation, BreederHQ was built for that.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What does EasyKeeper cost vs BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'EasyKeeper Essentials is $19/month ($209/year annual). Performance is $27/month ($297/year annual). Both per easykeeper.com/plans-and-pricing on July 1, 2026. Trial is 30 days, no credit card required. BreederHQ pricing is on our pricing page. First 100 founding subscribers use code FOUNDER50 for 50% off Pro or Enterprise for 12 months.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does EasyKeeper support species other than goats?',
    answer: 'No. EasyKeeper is explicitly a goat herd management platform. The homepage markets to "the modern goat breeder" and covers dairy, meat, fiber, and hobby/specialty goats. BreederHQ supports nine species in one account: dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, and cattle. If you run a mixed farm (goats plus LGDs, or goats plus sheep, or goats plus rabbits), that is one BreederHQ account, not two subscriptions.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does EasyKeeper have a mobile app?',
    answer: 'EasyKeeper does not publicly advertise dedicated iOS or Android apps. The homepage states, "No download required. Access your records online at any time on an internet-connected device," indicating a web-app-only model with browser access from a phone. BreederHQ ships native iOS and Android apps in addition to the web app, scoped specifically for on-the-go capture (kidding pen, milking stand, pasture, feed store, vet visit).'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does BreederHQ support DHIR / dairy production tracking the way EasyKeeper does?',
    answer: 'Not to EasyKeeper\'s current dairy-goat depth. EasyKeeper is the multi-year specialist on dairy goat production: milk yield by doe, lactation cycles, batch entry, DHIR integration. If your operation is dairy-goat-first and DHIR is core, EasyKeeper is the more mature product on that specific surface. BreederHQ tracks weight, growth, health, breeding, offspring, and financials across nine species, and adds capabilities (marketplace, buyer portal, embed widget, automation, mobile app, Scout AI) that EasyKeeper does not offer. Dairy production tracking is on the BreederHQ roadmap; we are honest that it is not shipped at EasyKeeper\'s current depth today.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does EasyKeeper have a marketplace or a way to sell kids?',
    answer: 'EasyKeeper is a herd management platform and does not publicly market a buyer-facing marketplace or a per-buyer client portal for kid placements. BreederHQ runs a transactional marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com where breeders publish listings for kids, breeding programs, and adult animals. When a kid is registered as born, a BreederHQ marketplace listing can be auto-generated from the program record. Sold kids drop from the listing automatically. If you sell kids off the farm, this is a real workflow difference.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I move my EasyKeeper records to BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ supports CSV import for animals, pedigrees, and contacts. Weight history, health events, and reproductive history can be imported if EasyKeeper provides CSV export. Photos and documents need re-upload. There is no one-click migration. Plan a few hours of setup or contact support@breederhq.com for scoping help. If EasyKeeper\'s export options are limited, raise that with their support before committing either direction. Data portability is a right, not a favor.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is EasyKeeper a good product?',
    answer: 'Yes. EasyKeeper reports managing approximately 90,000 goats as of June 2026, has been in the market for years, and has a strong community reputation among dairy-goat breeders. If dairy goats are your center of gravity and DHIR is core to your operation, EasyKeeper is the specialist. This page is not a "we are better at everything" argument. It is the honest version of when each tool is the right pick.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Which is better for a mixed farm (goats + livestock guardian dogs + rabbits)?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ. One account, one subscription, one login, one mental model. Nine species supported in the same account. EasyKeeper is goats-only and would leave the dog and rabbit sides of the operation on a separate tool.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Which is better for a small dairy goat operation with no plans to expand species?',
    answer: 'If dairy production tracking and DHIR are the daily workflow, EasyKeeper is the more specialized fit today at $19 or $27 per month. If you also sell kids, run a website, want a client portal for kid buyers, or want financial attribution per doe and per kidding, BreederHQ carries more of the operation but does not yet match EasyKeeper on dairy-specific depth. Both are legitimate choices for that profile.'
  }
];

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper: The Honest 2026 Comparison for Goat Breeders",
  "description": "BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper compared on pricing, species coverage, dairy tracking, marketplace, buyer portal, mobile app, and automation for goat breeders. Publicly verifiable facts, verified July 2026.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://breederhq.com/logo.svg"
    }
  },
  "image": "https://breederhq.com/og-image.jpg",
  "datePublished": "2026-07-01",
  "dateModified": "2026-07-01",
  "mainEntityOfPage": {
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://breederhq.com/compare/breederhq-vs-easykeeper"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper: The Honest 2026 Comparison"
  description="BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper compared on pricing, species coverage, dairy tracking, marketplace, buyer portal, and mobile for goat breeders. Verified July 2026."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />

  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
    <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
        <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
        <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
        <li><a href="/compare" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Compare</a></li>
        <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
        <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper: The Honest 2026 Comparison for Goat Breeders</h1>

        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Published: July 1, 2026 &middot; Last verified against easykeeper.com: July 1, 2026</p>

        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          EasyKeeper is the goat specialist, web-only, deep on dairy production and DHIR. BreederHQ is the multi-species operations-plus-marketplace-plus-buyer-flow platform with native mobile apps. Both are used by real goat breeders. Here is the honest version of when each one wins.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="https://accounts.breederhq.com/register" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-md bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white font-semibold hover:bg-[hsl(24,95%,48%)] transition">
            Start 14-day free trial
          </a>
          <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-md border-2 border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-semibold hover:border-gray-400 transition">
            See BreederHQ pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TL;DR -->
    <section class="py-12 px-4 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <aside class="bg-white border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 rounded shadow-sm" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">TL;DR</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong>Pick EasyKeeper if</strong> you run a goats-only operation, dairy production and DHIR are core to your daily work, and you do not need a marketplace, buyer portal, native mobile app, or per-buyer sales flow. EasyKeeper is the multi-year dairy-goat specialist, has ~90,000 goats under management (self-reported June 2026), and has a strong community reputation. Essentials is $19/month or $209/year; Performance is $27/month or $297/year.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Pick BreederHQ if</strong> you run goats plus another species, or you sell kids to buyers and want the buyer-facing surface built in, or you need native iOS and Android apps for capture in the kidding pen, or you want per-litter and per-kid financial attribution with quarterly tax export, or you want your own website to auto-update from your program records. BreederHQ trades EasyKeeper&apos;s dairy-goat depth for platform breadth: nine species, marketplace, buyer portal, embed widget, rules-based automation, Scout AI, and mobile.
          </p>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshot placeholder -->
    <section class="py-8 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <figure class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-8 bg-gray-50 text-center">
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">Illustration</div>
          <div class="text-lg text-gray-700 font-medium">BreederHQ mobile app: kidding pen weight capture</div>
          <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3">Weight entry from the mobile app during kidding, with body condition scoring, notes, and photo capture in one flow. Data lands in the herd record and rolls up to per-kid growth curves.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Comparison table -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Side-by-side: BreederHQ vs EasyKeeper</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Publicly verifiable facts only, sourced from easykeeper.com and breederhq.com. Verified July 1, 2026. Vendors change pricing and feature scope. Confirm on each site before committing.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-left">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Capability</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">EasyKeeper</th>
                <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">BreederHQ</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Entry price</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Essentials $19/mo ($209/yr); Performance $27/mo ($297/yr)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">See <a href="/pricing" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">pricing page</a>. FOUNDER50: 50% off Pro or Enterprise for 12 months.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Free trial length</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">30 days, no credit card</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">14 days</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Species supported</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Goats only (dairy, meat, fiber, hobby/specialty)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">9 (dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Dairy production tracking (milk yield, lactation)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes, mature depth. Performance tier includes milk production and batch entry.</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not at EasyKeeper&apos;s depth today. Health, weight, and growth tracked; dairy-specific milk-yield surface on roadmap.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">DHIR integration</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes (advertised)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not shipped</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Native mobile apps</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">No, web-only. "No download required. Access from an internet-connected device."</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: native iOS and Android apps + responsive web</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Public marketplace / buyer discovery</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Transactional marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Per-buyer client portal</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: records, photos, pedigree, contracts, invoices, messaging, documents</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Per-litter / per-animal financial attribution</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Contact management + reporting; not publicly advertised as per-litter cost allocation</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: per-litter and per-animal cost + revenue rollups; quarterly tax export</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Camera receipt-to-expense (mobile)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">No (no native mobile)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: Scout AI reads receipts, files vendor/date/amount/category to ledger</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">AI document extraction</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: Scout AI reads lab PDFs, vet invoices, photos</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Rules-based automation across offspring lifecycle</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: kid-born to listing-live to waitlist-opens to deposit-collected</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Website embed widget</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Not publicly advertised</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Yes: live listings syndicate to Squarespace, Wix, WordPress, Shopify, GoDaddy, HTML</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Photo storage</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Essentials: 5 photos per animal; Performance: unlimited</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Media Vault with generous storage on paid tiers; verify current limits on <a href="/pricing" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">pricing page</a></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Scale (self-reported)</th>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">~90,000 goats under management (June 2026)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Growing; founder-led; not disclosed publicly</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
          <strong>Last verified:</strong> July 1, 2026 against easykeeper.com/plans-and-pricing, easykeeper.com, easykeeper.com/features, and breederhq.com/pricing. Vendors change pricing and feature scope. Verify before committing. Corrections: <a href="mailto:support@breederhq.com" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">support@breederhq.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What goat breeders say -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">What EasyKeeper users actually say</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Direct quotes from public Capterra reviews of EasyKeeper and a first-person breeder blog. Not our characterization. Cited to the source.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <blockquote class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic mb-3">"Not able to tie into dairy record processing centers yet"</p>
            <cite class="text-sm text-gray-600 not-italic">
              Dennis E., Capterra review of EasyKeeper, December 5, 2018 &middot; <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/148787/EasyKeeper/reviews/" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">source</a>
            </cite>
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic mb-3">"No bulk entries for vaccination and worming but they are working on it!!"</p>
            <cite class="text-sm text-gray-600 not-italic">
              Jennifer A., Capterra review of EasyKeeper, October 19, 2016 &middot; <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/148787/EasyKeeper/reviews/" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">source</a>
            </cite>
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic mb-3">"I would like to track more financial aspects of feed and supplies."</p>
            <cite class="text-sm text-gray-600 not-italic">
              Sherry C., Capterra review of EasyKeeper, March 28, 2019 &middot; <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/148787/EasyKeeper/reviews/" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">source</a>
            </cite>
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic mb-3">"The price may be cost-prohibitive for smaller farms"</p>
            <cite class="text-sm text-gray-600 not-italic">
              Capterra reviewer, EasyKeeper &middot; <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/148787/EasyKeeper/reviews/" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">source</a>
            </cite>
          </blockquote>

          <blockquote class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-gray-300">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 italic mb-3">"To be able to see a goat's entire medical history at a glace is incredibly helpful."</p>
            <cite class="text-sm text-gray-600 not-italic">
              Capterra reviewer, EasyKeeper &middot; positive perspective &middot; <a href="https://www.capterra.com/p/148787/EasyKeeper/reviews/" rel="nofollow noopener" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">source</a>
            </cite>
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-8">
          EasyKeeper users like EasyKeeper. The critiques above are targeted (bulk vaccination entry, deeper financial tracking, DHIR-adjacent processing centers, entry-price accessibility for small farms), not fundamental. The tool is loved for what it is: a purpose-built goat-herd operations platform.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Where BreederHQ shows up in that context is not "EasyKeeper is bad." It is "EasyKeeper is a specialist, and your operation may have needs the specialist does not serve." The two most common reasons goat breeders reach for BreederHQ are (1) they run more than just goats, and (2) they want a marketplace, buyer portal, and website integration built into the platform their kids and their operation records live on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Where EasyKeeper wins -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Where EasyKeeper genuinely wins</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          A comparison page that only lists where the other tool falls short is not honest. Here is where EasyKeeper is the better pick on its own terms, and why we recommend it in those cases.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">1. Dairy production depth</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              EasyKeeper Performance tier includes milk production tracking, lactation cycles, body condition scoring, and batch entry. This has been developed over years specifically for dairy-goat operations, with input from working dairy breeders. If your daily workflow is milk-stand-first, EasyKeeper is the more specialized surface than BreederHQ today. BreederHQ tracks weight, health, breeding, and reproduction across species, and we are honest that dairy-specific milk-yield tracking at EasyKeeper&apos;s depth is on the roadmap, not shipped at that level today.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">2. DHIR integration</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              For dairy-goat breeders whose herd is enrolled in the Dairy Herd Improvement Registry, EasyKeeper&apos;s DHIR integration removes a category of data-entry work. BreederHQ does not offer DHIR integration today. This is a specialist advantage.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">3. Community reputation among goat breeders</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              EasyKeeper has been in the goat-breeder community long enough to be a known quantity. ~90,000 goats are reportedly managed on the platform. New adopters can find peers who have run their program on EasyKeeper for years. That kind of peer-verified stability is worth something.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">4. Longer free trial</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              30 days versus BreederHQ&apos;s 14. If you want a full kidding season or a full lactation milestone to land inside your evaluation window, those extra 16 days matter. Both approaches are legitimate. EasyKeeper&apos;s longer runway is genuinely useful for evaluating dairy-specific workflows.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">5. Goat-first mental model</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Every field, every workflow, every default in EasyKeeper is calibrated for goat operations. When you open a new-animal form, you are not routing through generic-livestock defaults. This kind of focus is real value if goats are all you run and all you plan to run.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Where BreederHQ is different -->
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Where BreederHQ is a categorically different product</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          These are capability differences, not opinion. Each is sourced from publicly listed features on both vendors&apos; sites as of July 1, 2026.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">1. Nine species in one account</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              If you run goats plus a livestock guardian dog line, plus a small flock of hair sheep, plus a few rabbits, BreederHQ is one account with one subscription running the whole operation. EasyKeeper is goats-only, so the other species live somewhere else, on some other subscription, with some other login. Cross-species record-keeping, financial attribution, and reporting all fragment.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
              For a homesteader-scale mixed farm or a serious multi-species operation, "one system for the whole operation" is a legitimate structural advantage that no goat-only tool can offer.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">2. Native iOS and Android mobile apps</h3>
